===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# {{context|strongly|_|vulgar|offensive}} An extremely contemptible person. (generally used as a term of abuse.)
#: ''Up against the wall, '''motherfucker'''.''
# {{context|strongly vulgar}} Any person, often but not always with the connotation that the person is disliked or is threatening.
#: ''Check out this '''motherfucker'''.''
# {{context|markedly vulgar}} An extremely intense experience, often but not always negative.
#: ''War is a '''motherfucker'''.''
#: ''I jammed my finger in the door yesterday. It hurt like a '''motherfucker'''.''
#: ''You mess with me, and I will come at you like a '''motherfucker'''.''
# {{context|teasingly|friendly|jokingly|vulgar}} A good very close friend or relative.
#: ''How’ve you been, you crazy '''motherfucker'''?''
# {{context|literally|vulgar}} One who engages in incest with their mother.
#* {{seeCites}}
# {{context|literally|vulgar}} One who engages in [[sex]] with a mother, not necessarily one's own.

